sbml2modelica.sbmlabstraction

Class ModelAbstractionManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • sbml2modelica.sbmlabstraction.ModelAbstractionManager

  • public class ModelAbstractionManager
extends java.lang.Object
    A ModelAbstractionManager provides functionalities for the generation of an AbstractModel from a given SBML Model.
    At first it computes the informations about the model. Then it generates the elements of the AbstractModel and, once every element has been generated, it generates all the values.
    Author:
    Maggioli Filippo

    • Method Detail

      • generateModel

        public void generateModel()
        This method generates the AbstractModel that represents the SBML Model.
        Generations involves three steps:
        • General informations about the model (default unit of measurements, parameters, ecc.).
        • Generation of the AbstractObjects that define the elements of the AbstractModel.
        • Generation of the AbstractValues that define the quantities and the equations in the AbstractModel.

      • getModel

        public AbstractModel getModel()
        This method returns the AbstractModel that represents the SBML Model with which the ModelAbstractionManager has been created.
        If the AbstractModel has not yet been generated the first time this method is called, then the AbstractModel is generated and then returned.
        All the subsequent times it is called, it simply returns the same AbstractModel, if it has not been recomputed or changed in other ways.
        Returns:
        The AbstractModel that represents the SBML Model of the ModelAbstractionManager.
